The article discusses the impact of the pandemic on women's labor force participation and the need for investment in infrastructure, care economy, and job opportunities to address the resulting gender and racial income and wealth gaps. President Biden's American Jobs Plan is highlighted as a solution that will create jobs, rebuild infrastructure, modernize schools and child care centers, and expand access to quality, affordable home- or community-based care for aging relatives and people with disabilities. The plan also aims to ensure fair pay, safe workplaces, and protection against discrimination and harassment for working women. Additionally, it includes investments in workforce development programs, career pathways, and support for women-owned small businesses and minority business enterprises. The plan further emphasizes the importance of eliminating gender and racial inequities in research and development and promoting healthy and safe communities through investments in violence prevention programs and affordable housing.